===2020 census===
As of the [[2020 United States census|2020 census]], Duncan had a population of 57, with 32 households and 23 families residing in the community.<ref name="Census2020DP">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic Profile (DP1)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dp?get=NAME,DP1_0021P,DP1_0024P,DP1_0025C,DP1_0049C,DP1_0045C,DP1_0069C,DP1_0073C,DP1_0125P,DP1_0126P,DP1_0129P,DP1_0133P,DP1_0137P,DP1_0138P,DP1_0139P,DP1_0141P,DP1_0142P,DP1_0143P,DP1_0145P,DP1_0146P,DP1_0147C,DP1_0148C,DP1_0149C,DP1_0156C,DP1_0157C,DP1_0158C,DP1_0159P,DP1_0160P&for=place%3A22710&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref><ref name="Census2020PL">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Redistricting Data (Public Law 94-171)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/pl?get=NAME,P1_001N,P1_003N,P1_004N,P1_005N,P1_006N,P1_007N,P1_008N,P1_009N,P2_001N,P2_002N,H1_001N,H1_002N&for=place%3A22710&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2021|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref> The [[population density]] was 72.6 inhabitants per square mile (28.0/km<sup>2</sup>). The median age was 48.3 years. 15.8% of residents were under the age of 18 and 29.8% were 65 years of age or older. For every 100 females, there were 171.4 males, and for every 100 females age 18 and over, there were 182.4 males age 18 and over.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

Of the 32 households, 37.5% had children under the age of 18 living with them, 68.8% were married-couple households, 9.4% were cohabiting-couple households, 18.8% were households with a male householder and no spouse or partner present, and 3.1% were households with a female householder and no spouse or partner present.<ref name="Census2020DP"/> 28.1% of all households were non-families. 21.9% of all households were made up of individuals, and 9.4% had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

There were 32 housing units at an average density of 40.7 per square mile (15.7/km<sup>2</sup>). Of all housing units, 0.0% were vacant. The homeowner vacancy rate was 0.0% and the rental vacancy rate was 0.0%.<ref name="Census2020DP"/> All residents lived in rural areas.<ref name="Census2020DHC">{{cite web|title=2020 Decennial Census Demographic and Housing Characteristics (DHC)|url=https://api.census.gov/data/2020/dec/dhc?get=NAME,P2_002N,P2_003N&for=place%3A22710&in=state%3A19|website=United States Census Bureau|year=2023|access-date=May 1, 2026|df=mdy}}</ref>

The age distribution was 17.5% under the age of 20, 1.8% from 20 to 24, 26.3% from 25 to 44, 24.6% from 45 to 64, and 29.8% age 65 or older. The gender makeup was 63.2% male and 36.8% female.<ref name="Census2020DP"/>

